        "text_twGGkJ": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Skin that shines through the day, especially across the forehead and nose, with more visible pores. Oily skin makes more surface oil than it strictly needs, but it rarely reacts, and its natural oiliness gives it some protection. It doesn't want stripping back. It wants light hydration that works with it, and that's what this part of the range is built to give it.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-primary--family)",
            "font_size": "",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_AkCqgY": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Is this you?</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_9yPipQ": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Oily skin tends to shine by the middle of the day, particularly across the T-zone. Make-up may start to slide, a tissue pressed to the skin comes away with a shine, and pores are usually easier to see. What it doesn't often do is feel tight, flake, or react badly to new products.<br/><br/>If your skin is more shine than tightness and generally takes things in its stride, you're in the right place. If you're not sure, the <a href=\"/pages/find-your-skin-type\" title=\"Find Your Skin Type\">skin type finder</a> will point you the right way.<br/></p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_ECWcka": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>What this skin type needs</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_hiULWP": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Oily skin gets more advice thrown at it than any other type, most of it about stripping the oil away. That tends to backfire, because skin stripped of its oil often responds by making more. So the approach here is the opposite of a fight. Light hydration from oils chosen to suit oily skin, to support it rather than provoke it.<br/><br/>Oily skin still needs moisture, and skipping it altogether is a common way to end up shinier, not less. So the oils are light and low-comedogenic, and the textures are kept as light as the range goes. Support, not strip.<br/></p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_7Ck6rn": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The oils we chose for it</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_kfnJJB": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Every Oily moisturiser shares the same blend of four cold-pressed organic oils, chosen for this skin type, and it's the lightest blend in the range.<br/><br/><a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/grape-vitis-vinifera-seed-oil\" title=\"Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Seed Oil\">Grape </a>seed is a light, fast-absorbing oil high in linoleic acid, the essential fatty acid the skin uses to keep its barrier in order, and a natural fit for oily skin. <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/rose-hip-rosa-canina-seed-oil\" title=\"Rosa Canina (Rose Hip) Fruit Oil\">Rose </a>hip is similarly light and linoleic-rich, and the research credits it with supporting skin texture and tone. <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/argan-argania-spinosa-kernel-oil\" title=\"Argania Spinosa (Argan) Kernel Oil\">Argan </a>sits at a modest level as a conditioning note, described for its fatty acids and vitamin E rather than the marketing that tends to surround it. And <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/dragon-fruit-hylocereus-undatus-seed-oil\" title=\"Hylocereus Undatus (Dragon Fruit) Fruit Extract\">dragon fruit </a>seed oil adds a light, well-balanced profile.<br/><br/>Around those four sits a supporting cast shared across the whole range. <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/squalane\" title=\"Squalane\">Squalane</a>, a lightweight oil close to one the skin makes for itself. Soothing <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/allantoin\" title=\"Allantoin\">allantoin</a>. A prebiotic and postbiotic pairing chosen to support the skin's own microbiome, where the evidence is still emerging and we would rather say so than overstate it. And our signature <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/bladder-wrack-fucus-vesiculosus-extract\" title=\"Fucus Vesiculosus (Bladderwrack) Extract\">bladderwrack</a>, the same Atlantic seaweed species we know from the rocks below Welcombe, though the extract itself is produced in France from that species. The coast is the kinship here, not the supply chain.<br/><br/>Every ingredient, and the exact amount of each, is published on each product page. That's the whole point of how we work, and each one links through to its own page if you want to read further.<br/></p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_NkE9Xj": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Your three moisturisers</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_cTGRCz": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The same Oily blend comes in three textures, so you can match the richness to where you're using it. All three stay light, since that's what this skin type is after.<br/><br/><strong>Flow </strong>is the lightest, made for the face. <strong>Core </strong>is a touch richer, for the body. <strong>Deep </strong>is the richest of the three, for the areas that turn dry even on oily skin, the hands, elbows and feet.<br/><br/>Same blend throughout. More or less of it, depending on what the skin is asking for.<br/></p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        }
