            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_ahKGbw": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>A couple of habits help oily skin far more than any amount of stripping does.<br/><br/>Don't skip moisturiser. It's the single most common mistake with oily skin, and going without often leaves the skin drier underneath and oilier on top. Cleanse gently rather than harshly, with lukewarm water, since hot water and aggressive cleansers strip the skin and prompt it to make even more oil to compensate. Reach for lighter textures. And give antioxidants and sensible sun protection a place, both of which suit this skin type well. Working with your skin beats waging war on it.<br/><br/>You'll have noticed we never use synthetic fragrance. There's a single essential oil in the range, <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/vetiver-vetiveria-zizanioides-root-oil\" title=\"Vetiveria Zizanoides (Vetiver) Root Oil\">vetiver</a>, at a low level and chosen on purpose, and it appears on every label so you can see exactly how much is there.<br/></p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_iiUCEX": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Your skin can settle over time</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_hVYV6M": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Oily isn't a fixed label. Looked after steadily, without the stripping that provokes more oil, oily skin often calms down over time, and for some people it gradually settles toward the steadier Balanced type. It's gradual, it comes from working with your skin rather than against it rather than from any single product working magic, and it's a good reason to treat where your skin is today as a starting point. If it changes, the skin type finder is always there to place yourself again.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
